{"article_id":"nDuiES3NLOr67frz","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON-President Trump accused Google of elevating critical news stories about his presidency at the expense of friendly conservative voices ,","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"signaling potential government action","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"if it didn ' t change its alleged practices .","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"Mr. Trump complained Tuesday on Twitter","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"that Google search results for the words \" Trump news \" returned results primarily from what he labeled \" Left-Wing Media.","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"\" Google and others \" are suppressing voices of Conservatives","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"and hiding information and news","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"that is good , \"","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"he wrote .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"He said","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"the way","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"such sites present results","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"is a \" very serious situation","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"-- will be addressed . \"","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Later , in remarks at the White House , Mr. Trump said","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"companies including Google , Facebook Inc. and Twitter Inc.","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"are \" treading on very , very troubling territory \"","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"and warned :","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"\" They better be careful","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"because you can ' t do that to people . \"","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"The allegations come","depth":4},{"id":21,"text":"as some policy makers in Washington have voiced concerns about a number of practices by Google , a unit of Alphabet Inc. ,","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"including whether it is stifling competition","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"and endangering the privacy of billions of users .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"Members of Congress questioned Google and other tech giants earlier this year over allegations","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"that their platforms favored liberal voices over conservative ones .","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"A Google spokeswoman said","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"its search results aren ' t biased toward a particular political ideology .","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"\" We continually work","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"to improve Google Search","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"and we never rank search results","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"to manipulate political sentiment , \"","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"she said in a statement .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"Related Video","depth":3},{"id":34,"text":"Google handles 90 % of the world 's internet searches ,","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"and it increasingly is promoting a single answer for many questions .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"Even subjective or unanswerable queries sometimes get seemingly definitive answers .","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"Here 's how the algorithms are-and aren ' t-working .","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"Video/Photo Illustration :","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"Heather Seidel/The Wall Street Journal","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"A Facebook spokesman declined to comment .","depth":5},{"id":41,"text":"A spokesman for Twitter didn ' t respond to a request for comment .","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"Lawmakers are also concerned about the role","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"social media played","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"in amplifying alleged efforts by Russia","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"to interfere in the 2016 elections .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"On Sept. 5 , executives","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"including Twitter Chief Executive Jack Dorsey and Facebook Chief Operating Officer Sheryl Sandberg","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"are scheduled to testify before the Senate Intelligence Committee about election interference .","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"Other issues , such as alleged bias , are also expected to be raised during the hearing .","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"Kent Walker , Google ' s senior vice president for global affairs , planned to join the hearing .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"But last week , Sen. Richard Burr","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"( R. , N.C. ) ,","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"who heads that committee ,","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"said","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"he had rejected Google ' s offer","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"to send Mr. Walker , apparently in an effort","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"to force a more-senior executive to appear .","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"In his tweets Tuesday , Mr. Trump questioned","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"whether Google ' s purported political bias may be \" illegal \"","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"but didn ' t elaborate on what he meant","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"when he said","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"the issue will be addressed .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"A White House official said","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"the Republican president has made clear","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"he wants his administration to look into the issue","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"and several officials were tasked on Tuesday with finding options for potential action against social media companies .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"\" It ' s starting now , \"","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"the official said .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"It wasn ' t known what steps Mr. Trump could take","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"to put pressure on the companies","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"besides continuing his public criticisms .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"While government agencies","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"including the Justice Department , Federal Trade Commission and Federal Communications Commission","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"have powers","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"to regulate U.S. companies ,","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"they operate independently from the White House","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"and haven ' t always acted in ways","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"Mr. Trump favors .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"For instance , in July Mr. Trump complained about the FCC ' s decision","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"to block Sinclair Broadcast Group ' s merger with Tribune Media Co.","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"\" So sad and unfair , \"","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"he tweeted .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"There are few tools","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"the administration could use","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"to directly regulate how internet companies present search results and other content","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"without running afoul of the First Amendment .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"But the administration could target related issues","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"to make life difficult for them .","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"For example , the White House could urge allies in Congress to change Section 230 of the Communications Decency Act , a landmark law","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"that shields internet companies from liability","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"for hosting content","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"produced by others .","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"It could also push for investigations of online privacy violations .","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"Both issues have attracted support from Democrats as well as Republicans .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"\" It ' s clear to me and to most people that there is not bias in search","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"and there is not bias in social media , \"","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"said Michael Beckerman , president and CEO of the Internet Association ,","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"which represents tech companies","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"including Google","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"on regulatory issues .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"Still ,","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"on the potential for further regulation ,","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"\" You always have to take these things very seriously . \"","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"Mr. Trump ' s longstanding criticism of the media adds to the difficulty","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"of evaluating his claims .","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"He has frequently charged","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"that news outlets broadly are biased against him ,","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"saying last month","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"that \" a large percentage \" of the media are \" fake news , \"","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"making it likely that even a statistically neutral news aggregator would pull heavily from sources","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"he labels that way .","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"Last week , the president accused social-media platforms of \" silencing millions of people \"","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"by shutting down accounts .","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"Earlier in the month , he claimed","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"tech companies are \" totally discriminating against Republican/Conservative voices , \"","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"pledging","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"that his administration \" won ' t let that happen . \"","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"In recent weeks , Facebook , Apple Inc. , Alphabet ' s YouTube platform and Spotify Technology SA stripped their sites of content from far-right conspiracy theorist Alex Jones ,","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"saying","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"the Infowars star had violated terms of service","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"barring certain hateful or offensive speech .","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"Mr. Jones retains his Twitter account .","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"In April , House Judiciary Committee Chairman Bob Goodlatte","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"( R. , Va. )","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"warned tech executives in a hearing","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"while social media companies were \" exercising great care and discretion","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"to ensure","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"that their services are not abused ,","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"\" there is a \" fine line","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"between removing illegal activity","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"and suppressing speech . \"","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"Google News ' s search algorithm is opaque ,","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"and news media outlets expend considerable energy and resources","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"optimizing their online content","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"to win better placement in search results .","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"Google ' s search engine is calibrated","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"to show web links","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"a user is most likely to follow ,","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"based on which links were the most popular with previous searches of the same keyword .","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"The company also takes into account where a user is located , what time of day it is and other signals","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"that help it tailor search results for each user .","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"It is unlikely Google ' s system measures","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"whether a particular news article is right-leaning or left-leaning ,","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"said Steven Andres , a professor of management information systems at San Diego State University .","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"\" They only categorize things by relevance , \"","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"Dr. Andres said .","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"\" They are trying to maximize profits . \"","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"Google forged ties to Democrats under President Obama ,","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"helping fuel the suspicions of conservatives .","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"Google employees donated $ 1.6 million to Hillary Clinton ' s campaign , about 80 % more than the amount","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"given by workers at any other corporation ,","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"and its former executive chairman , Eric Schmidt , helped set up companies","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"to analyze political data for Mrs. Clinton ' s campaign .","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"In one instance , a widely shared video alleged","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"that Google ' s autocomplete service ,","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"which tries to predict queries","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"as users type ,","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"was biased toward Mrs. Clinton .","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"According to the video ,","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"typing \" Hillary Clinton cri \" into a Google search box yielded suggested queries","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"related to crime reform , crisis , and a crime bill .","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"It didn ' t include the suggested search \" Hillary Clinton crimes . \"","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"Google said in response","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"that said","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"the autocomplete software won ' t show \" a predicted query","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"that is offensive or disparaging","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"when displayed in conjunction with a person ' s name. \"","depth":13},{"id":170,"text":"A person familiar with the software said","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"the word \" crimes \" was included in the list of offensive terms .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":343,"left":204,"right":342,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":191,"right":203,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":191,"left":174,"right":190,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":0,"right":173,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":190,"left":184,"right":189,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":184,"left":175,"right":183,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":183,"left":178,"right":182,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":177,"right":8,"relat